{
  "texts": [
    "In this context, nodes symbolize the co-cited documents, while the edges between them denote instances of co-citation.",
    "The size of a node correlates with the frequency of document occurrence, with more frequently occurring papers having larger nodes.",
    "Similarly, the thickness of the edges corresponds to the frequency of co-occurrence, with more frequently co-occurring records having thicker edges.",
    "As depicted in Fig. 10 co-cited by other source documents.",
    "The research fields associated with the records are represented by the colours of the nodes in the co-citation network."
  ]
}